  <h1>
   part_type_alpha1
  </h1>
  This function is used to set a particle type to have a single alpha value (transparency) for the total duration of the lifetime of each individual particle, and this can be from 0 (transparent) to 1 (opaque).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">part_type_alpha1(ind, alpha1);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      ind
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Particles/Particle_Types/part_type_create.htm">
        Particle Type ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the particle type to change.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      alpha1
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The alpha of the particle.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">part_type_alpha1(global.Snow_Part, 0.5);
</code></pre>
  The above code will set all particles created of the particle type indexed in the global variable "Snow_Part" to have an alpha value of 0.5 (semi-transparent).
 </body>
</html>